President Obama has nominated Todd E. Edelman and Judge Judith Anne Smith as Associate Judges for the Superior Court of the District of Columbia. Edelman is a Visiting Associate Professor of Law at Georgetown University Law Center and has experience in civil litigation and criminal defense. Judge Smith currently serves as a magistrate judge on the Superior Court of the District of Columbia and has a background in special education and juvenile justice law. Both nominees have demonstrated a commitment to justice and public service throughout their careers.